article.headline: Temple 80, Penn 64
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Dionte Christmas scored 24 points and Mark Tyndale had 18 as Temple won its third straight game, 80-64 over city rival Penn on Wednesday night. Ryan Brooks added 14 points for the Owls (9-8), coached by Fran Dunphy, who is in his second season at Temple after coaching Penn for 17 years. Tyler Bernardini had 16 second-half points for the Quakers (5-12). Jack Eggleston added 15. Temple was in command throughout, and led 65-48 with 6:27 remaining. The Quakers then used a 9-2 run to close within 67-57, but Tyndale scored on a layup and Christmas hit a jumper to end the threat. The Owls scored the first 12 points of the game, hitting on four straight 3-pointers, while Penn was turning the ball over three times. The Owls raced to a 31-14 advantage on a 3-pointer by Chris Clark. After Penn scored five straight points, Temple used a 10-3 run to take a 41-22 lead at the half.
